t: "O Prophet! We have made lawful for you your wives to whom you have paid their Ë¹fullËº dowries as well as those Ë¹bondwomenËº in your possession, whom God has granted you.Â And Ë¹you are allowed to marryËº the daughters of your paternal uncles and aunts, and the daughters of your maternal uncles and aunts, who have emigrated like you. Also Ë¹allowed for marriage isËº a believing woman who offers herself to the Prophet Ë¹without dowryËº if he is interested in marrying herâ€”Ë¹this isËº exclusively for you, not for the rest of the believers.Â We know well what Ë¹rulingsËº We have ordained for the believers in relation to their wives and those Ë¹bondwomenËº in their possession. As such, there would be no blame on you. And God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"